article.headline: Utah Valley St. 65, Chicago St. 56
article.story: OREM, Utah -- Holton Hunsaker scored 18 points and Geddes Robinson had 10 points and 16 rebounds Thursday night as Utah Valley rallied to defeat Chicago State 65-56. Isiah Williams added 13 points and Keith Thompson scored 12 for the Wolverines (12-10, 2-0 Great West), who trailed by eight late in the first half but were only down 34-31 at intermission. Utah Valley used a 10-0 run early in the second half to take the lead for good. Jeremy Robinson had 18 points and 13 rebounds for the Cougars (2-18, 1-2). Ardarius Simmons made 5 of 6 3-point attempts and also finished with 18 points for Chicago State, while Clarke Rosenberg added 12 points. The Cougars are winless in 14 road games this season.
